Pronotal sides (Fig. 279) on posterior half feebly convergent anteriorly, on anterior half strongly convergent, apical angles produced, marginal pronotal stria complete, carinate, behind head medially with tiny angulate projection; disc antero-laterally with deep, rugulose-lacunose oval punctation, medially punctures becoming much sparser and finer, separated by several times their diameter, forming vague impunctate areas (in some specimens these can be better delimited forming 
'mirrors'
), interspaces between punctures on entire pronotal disc with sparse microscopic punctation; pronotal hypomeron glabrous; scutellum very small.
